- 'Top 3 stocks' refers to the stocks with the highest average trading volumes; 
- 'Past month' refers to the time period from the current date to one month ago; 
- 'Average trading volumes' refers to the mean volume of shares traded for each stock; 
- 'Technical indicators' are mathematical calculations based on a stock's price and/or volume; 
- 'Analysis values' and 'descriptions' refer to the results of the technical analysis for each stock.

- Performance refers to the percentage change in the stock's closing price over the past 60 days relative to its 60-day average closing price; 
- A higher performance value indicates better performance; 
- Popularity is determined by the number of distinct users who have added the stock to their watchlist.
